Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Ostanin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 8 TASS -- Around 30 armed militants 
made an attempt to illegally cross from Afghanistan into 
Tajikistan on Monday night, in the area of the 12th Pyandzh 
border guard post controlled by Russian border guards, ITAR-TASS 
learned on Tuesday [8 February] from the press-service of 
Russian border guard troops. 
  The militants seized one of Tajik islands on the Pyandzh 
river. Their positions came under fire opened by the Tajik side, 
afterwards, the militants retreated to the adjoining territory, 
the same source said. 

